items.name: Odo
items.description:
Simple Lora for generating Odo from Deep Space Nine (Played by the late Rene Auberjonois).

Now updated for SDXL! I'm still learning how to fine-tune SDXL but my first attempts are already even better than anything a 1.5 LoRA could do.

It's a little bit overtrained, so I recommend a Lora strength of 0.8 or lower.

Only tested on the base SDXL model. Do not use the SDXL refiner or it ruins the Odo likeness.

modelVersions.name: OdoXL v001 (alpha)
modelVersions.description: This is only my second attempt to train a version of the Odo model on SDXL. Dataset is slightly changed, including some more images of Odo in alternate outfits so it does slightly better at clothing other than his normal uniform. Trained in 4 epochs on a 3080 in ~25min, I'm pretty impressed with how easy SDXL fine-tuning really is once you get the right parameters to get it working at all.

Edit:
So i forgot some images that i use for the preview using control net when looking for pose or propotions, Here some guide to use ControlNet

  • Go towards extensions tabs and install this extension, https://github.com/Mikubill/sd-webui-controlnet

  • Download ControlNet model (https://huggingface.co/lllyasviel/ControlNet/tree/main/models) (recomended the openpose one) and place it inside sd-webui-controlnet/models extension folder

  • After installing, a tab named Control Net should be appeared in txt2img or img2img

  • Open the tab and use this image as a guidelines, pretty much use openpose preprocessor and openpose model then place the image that you want to use inside the tab.

  • Sometimes this method not working, you can use openpose stickman instead, here my collection of openpose stickman (set preprocessor to none like this)

  • Then just generate images like usual, just leave the ControlNet enabled. the image should resemble the pose

items.name: Female Armpit Hair - Concept
items.description:
Please read, this is not a plug and play LORA!


To effectively use this LORA you will need to use (armpit hair:1.3), or (armpit hair:1.4), or (armpit hair:1.5) and a low weight on the LORA, around 0.3-0.45... GOING HIGHER WILL MAKE BAD IMAGES.

As for other quirks:
1. You pretty much have to use high res fix for the best results, something about it's magic helps alot.

2. It's pretty much gacha if the armpit hair is in the right spot or size, but it's about 80% accurate. Playing with the weights of the tag and LORA can help though.

3. This LORA will pretty much force the arms up position. If you are looking for more a hair peek, then you will have to inpaint, which this LORA gives you the ability to do. Simply turn on the LORA, select Only Masked or whole image depending on the situation, use your regular Negative Prompt, and in the positives use: "<color> hair, armpit hair" and boom, you can inpaint armpit hair. The picture of the lady with the green hair (Maho) was made using inpaint

4. Weird hair colors may be hard to produce, blue, red or purple may take many tries, and you will have to play with the weights of the tag and LORA to get it right. Brown and Black work without much fuss. White doesn't work at all.

5, This lora has a tendency to make nipples appear through clothing, due to the rather degenerate dataset. If this is not something you want, add "nipples" and "skin tight" to your negatives.

Have fun!

items.name: Guilingao
items.description:
Based on a fusion of dreambox-mix, cetusMix_cetusVersion2 and Counterfeit-V2.5.

The EasyNegative program is required to restore the images in the example. If this is the first time you have heard of EasyNegative you can get a brief overview and download it here https://huggingface.co/datasets/gsdf/EasyNegative

Please ensure that the Hires. fix function is used when generating images, my usual settings are Denoising strength: 0.6, Hires upscale: 2, Hires steps: 12-20, Hires upscaler: Latent. With Steps: 20-24, Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras, CFG scale: 8-10 are used for generating 576x768 images. I usually use "((masterpiece, best quality))," as the start of a positive prompt and "EasyNegative," as the start of a negative prompt.

It was originally made with the intention of being able to draw fantasy medieval (or some kind of JRPG setting) in an alternative setting to my own satisfaction. As this is a spur-of-the-moment piece to satisfy personal preference, it has not been fully tested and may not be suitable for pictures in certain settings. In addition, my experience of using it shows that its positive prompt has problems with erratic image generation at less than 40 and more than 200. I have not been able to carry out similar tests with the negative prompt due to my use of EasyNegative (as the use of EasyNegative puts the negative prompt at 20-50 on a regular basis). If this is the first time you have heard of EasyNegative you can get a brief overview and download it here https://huggingface.co/datasets/gsdf/EasyNegative

I would be honoured if it produced wallpapers or avatars to your satisfaction.

Please do not use it commercially or in a way that might infringe on the portrait rights of others.

(Based on DeepL Chinese to English translation, which may be inaccurate.)

还原示例中的图片需要EasyNegative程序。如果第一次听说EasyNegative你可以在此简要了解并下载它https://huggingface.co/datasets/gsdf/EasyNegative

由于最初的目的是能够画出另自己满意背景下幻想中世纪（或是说某类JRPG背景，像是“为美好的世界献上祝福”那类的世界观）的作画而进行制作。由于仅是一时兴起为满足个人喜好的作品，它没有进行充分的测试，可能并不适应某些背景下的图片。此外，个人的使用经验显示其正prompt在小于40和大于200的情况下会出现图片生成不稳定的问题，而负 prompt由于个人使用EasyNegative的原因未能进行过类似测试（因为EasyNegative的运用使负prompt经常在20-50）。如果第一次听说EasyNegative你可以在此简要了解并下载它https://huggingface.co/datasets/gsdf/EasyNegative

The LoRAs included are trained locally on the kohya_ss GUI repository created by bmaltais as well as on the Google colab notebook for kohya LoRA.

The local version is trained on resolution 768 x 768 pixles while the colab notebook version is trained on resolution 512 x 512 pixels.

Images were produced using anything 4.5 pruned checkpoint in combination. Some generations used character LoRAs @Lykon character LoRAs such as Lucy from Cyberpunk Edgerunners and Aqua from the Kingdom Hearts series.

items.name: Robert Downey Jr. LoRA
items.description:
This man needs no introduction. You know him, we love him.

Support me on KO-FI so I can afford more rendertime, thank you :)

Or leave a rating, both would be appreciated.

And this might just be the best working LoRA I've created so far. The prompts I've tried were just a few minutes of experimentation, and literally 8/10 worked on the first shot.

It just works.

The training was done with the kohya LoRA model, so it requires the LoRa extension for Automatic1111 to function.

The model was trained against RealisticVision 1.3 but produces good results with artEros, hasdX and uberrealisticDreamy as well. Please read the rest of the description for more details.

I've used 50 Steps, CFG of 7 and a model strength of 0,9 for all images, the prompts were standard short model photoshoots, see the examples for the actual prompts used for each image.

One recommendation, try to avoid the word "suit". It was almost impossible to find pictures of this man where he doesn't wear a suit, and so the dataset was heavily biased towards suit pictures. Use the word "armor" or "cosplay" instead to put him in different outfits.
